#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:11
#: 5def20c6f59d4b85a9ec80e0d4bd12bf
msgid "What are bind-dirs?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:13
#: a19704fb5dbd442989b183979120d200
msgid ""
"With [bind-dirs](https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-agent-"
"linux/blob/master/vm-systemd/bind-dirs.sh) any arbitrary files or folders "
"can be made persistent in app qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:16
#: 8d9e4019cdcc40e382e726a419e7afbd
msgid "What is it useful for?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:18
#: f06299ffd52f4038bdd1babc9004f5c0
msgid ""
"In an app qube all of the file system comes from the template except "
"`/home`, `/usr/local`, and `/rw`. This means that changes in the rest of the"
" filesystem are lost when the app qube is shutdown. bind-dirs provides a "
"mechanism whereby files usually taken from the template can be persisted "
"across reboots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:22
#: 02cf30f3d6e04a38aae57aa46d19ad77
msgid ""
"For example, in Whonix, [Tor's data dir `/var/lib/tor` has been made "
"persistent in the TemplateBased ProxyVM sys-"
"whonix](https://github.com/Whonix/qubes-"
"whonix/blob/8438d13d75822e9ea800b9eb6024063f476636ff/usr/lib/qubes-bind-"
"dirs.d/40_qubes-whonix.conf#L5) In this way sys-whonix can benefit from the "
"Tor anonymity feature 'persistent Tor entry guards' but does not have to be "
"a standalone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:25
#: 6f620140cc5f4b8ba6125832ed64b42b
msgid "How to use bind-dirs.sh?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:27
#: 3a5eebacc43541999c6f110bb29ab13c
msgid "In this example, we want to make `/var/lib/tor` persistent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:29
#: 52be3c95f8634f159762007920966e76
msgid "Inside the app qube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:31
#: c44b915c86214a3392cfb5555b39f819
msgid "Make sure folder `/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d` exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:37
#: ad2c0ef974f346b590935143424b535e
msgid ""
"Create a file `/rw/config/qubes-bind-dirs.d/50_user.conf` with root rights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:39
#: b67c80d315254bab82a0f004796725b6
msgid ""
"Edit the file 50_user.conf to append a folder or file name to the `binds` "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:45
#: 7e71307705a64ce18291a8dfeae29d32
msgid "Save."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:47
#: 6596f3e4a0e84ac9993659664e4505f9
msgid "Reboot the app qube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:49
#: 654d168fc5e0406fac82b0e667729df6
msgid "Done."
msgstr "Fertig."

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:51
#: 20f99a2a05724b8986431b609f9489db
msgid ""
"From now on any files within the `/var/lib/tor` folder will persist across "
"reboots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:53
#: afb8d76a47e248f680bebdcf59d0410c
msgid ""
"You can make make many files or folders persist, simply by making multiple "
"entries in the `50_user.conf` file, each on a separate line. For example, if"
" you added the file `/etc/tor/torrc` to the `binds` variable, any "
"modifications to *that* file will persist across reboots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/advanced-topics/bind-dirs.md:61
#: 9b271dce28fd417989f6304b2451d77e
